The performance featured her singing a medley, including her song "Make Me" and a duet with G-Eazy on "Me, Myself & I." Spears explained that her microphone was muted to prevent any live vocals from being heard, with the intent to have only the pre-recorded track play. She expressed frustration over this decision, feeling it undermined her as a performer. Spears has long faced criticism and scrutiny over her use of pre-recorded tracks during live performances, and this incident highlighted the control her team exerted over her career, even during such a high-profile event.
